&lt;p&gt;Our work to make environmental data and science more accessible through software solutions and AI is growing. We’re responding to the sustained and growing ambitions of our partners in Europe – ESA, ECMWF, EUMETSAT, and “New Space”.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join us as Technical Project Lead and help us scale our work in Europe. You&#39;ll lead projects once they&#39;re awarded, and contribute to shaping and writing the proposals for our next contributions. The role combines project management with product ownership, focusing on project delivery, the technical approach on proposals, and the relationships that tie our global efforts together.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Since our work is to apply novel technology to production platforms or show how new approaches can scale, this role requires a strong technical understanding alongside solid project delivery. Your role is to connect our partner with our technical team and contribute with your strategic guidance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re a new, small and lean player in the European tech services sector, and pride ourselves to stand out as open, pragmatic, and professional. Are you inspired by this? Contribute to shaping how we build our practice&amp;nbsp;and reputation, working as a nimble partner alongside much larger organisations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a remote-first position. You need to be working from one of the&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.esa.int/About_Us/Corporate_news/Member_States_Cooperating_States&quot;&gt; ESA member states&lt;/a&gt;, with the option to work out of our office in Lisbon, Portugal. You&#39;ll focus on our European projects and partners while being part of our global team. We&#39;re aiming for a summer 2026 start.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own project management and product ownership on awarded projects: scope, work packages, costing, planning, backlog, and prioritisation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be a trusted point of contact to ESA, ECMWF, and EUMETSAT technical and contract officers, consortium partners, and the wider landscape&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute with delivery and field experience to our business development, supporting the proposal team on the technical approach and doing the hands-on technical writing on EU proposals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Connect the dots across related efforts so proposals and delivery reinforce each other&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What We&#39;re Looking For&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience leading technical projects as a lead engineer, project manager, or product owner, in environments where you stayed close to the engineering work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A strong technical understanding of our domain, comfortable coordinating research &amp;amp; development as well as operational application engineering&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid project management discipline: quarterly scoping and tracking, realistic costing, governance, and version control. You keep complex work moving across multiple partners and deliver on what&#39;s committed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience contributing to or leading proposals, including the hands-on technical writing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of the European Earth observation, geospatial, and space landscape and how it operates: programmes, procurement, and stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills and attention to detail. Fluent in English, with additional European languages a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Based in an ESA member state in Europe, for eligibility and travel and time zone compatibility&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Nice to Have&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An existing network across European partners like ESA, VITO, DLR, thriveGEO, EOX, Telespazio, CNES et al.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience writing or leading ESA or EU competitive proposals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with cloud-native data formats and architectures and geospatial specifications and technologies such as OGC API, STAC, TiTil

&lt;p&gt;Not seeing any available positions that match your skills &amp;amp; interests? Consider getting in touch via our general application. We may not respond as quickly as if you were to apply to a specific position, but we’ll keep your information on hand until the next position opens that’s relevant to you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We often announce openings for new positions, and will email you when a new opportunity comes up that fits your experience and interests.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Development Seed embraces diversity and equal opportunity in a serious way. We are committed to building a team that represents a variety of backgrounds, perspectives, and skills. The more inclusive we are, the better our work will be.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We have a strong, growing partnership with NASA around our shared commitment to advance open science in the cloud, push the boundaries of AI-driven Earth science, and build tools that magnify the impact of publicly funded research and data. Our NASA work spans multiple projects and is expanding in scope.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a technically-grounded project lead to work across our growing NASA portfolio. You&#39;ll bring real technical expertise and engineering leadership to cross-project coordination, stakeholder management, and project strategy. This is a leadership role: you&#39;ll be owning outcomes, representing Development Seed in technical forums with NASA, and helping shape how we deliver across multiple projects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Engineering credibility is central to this role. We lead the engineering and software development side of these partnerships, while NASA program managers navigate the larger institution. You’ll be a complement to those skills, not a replacement. That means you&#39;re comfortable going deep in technical conversations, giving meaningful direction to our engineering teams, and earning trust in rooms full of engineers and scientists. You won&#39;t be writing code day to day, but your background in engineering is what makes you effective.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll also be Development Seed&#39;s most consistent presence with our NASA partners at Marshall Space Flight Center, representing who we are and how we work: collaborative, curious, open-source oriented, and motivated by impact. &lt;strong&gt;Being local to the Huntsville area is a requirement&lt;/strong&gt;, as regular in-person time with our partners builds the kind of trust and credibility that&#39;s hard to replicate remotely.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Development Seed is a unique and rewarding place to do this work. Over the past two decades, we have honed our approach to stewarding projects from opportunity to successful, impactful products. Our partners are working on exciting and important problems. Our technical teams are built of curious, empathetic people with high intrinsic motivation and individual agency. We’re open-source by default, we invest heavily in research and development that drives the field, and we’re regularly reinventing the nature of our work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a hybrid position with regular on-site presence at NASA Marshall Space Flight Center in Huntsville, Alabama, as regular in-person time with our NASA partners is valuable for building the kind of relationships that make this role work. You should have working hours compatible with US Central or Eastern time. You&#39;ll also attend key conferences and occasionally travel to work with our global team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a bridge between NASA stakeholders and Development Seed&#39;s engineering teams, reducing communication cycles and keeping projects aligned&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead coordination across a portfolio of NASA projects, working with program managers, project teams, and technical experts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own project scope, objectives, and timelines, and ensure teams have the resources and support to deliver&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent Development Seed in forums and meetings with NASA and partners, bringing technical credibility and our team&#39;s perspective&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build trusted relationships with key stakeholders and proactively identify ways for us to better support them&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with other project leads to balance priorities across our NASA portfolio&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help identify and shape new opportunities that emerge from our partnership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
